# MAREfile
# This file is used by the maureen application to generate meta-data of the C++ namespaces, classes and structs.
# This meta-data is used by mirror-lib to provide compile-time introspection and reflection.

# See man maureen for more details regarding the syntax of this file.

# Input pattern
# Process hpp files in the src/common, src/fs and src/modules directories and their subdirectories, register everything
# (namespaces, classes, enums, etc.), in any namespace.
# Output pattern
# Place the output files in the src directory, at the same paths that the input files had.
'src/common||%|hpp|%|%|%' 'src/common|$(path)|$(file)|meta.$(suffix)'
'src/fs||%|hpp|%|%|%' 'src/fs|$(path)|$(file)|meta.$(suffix)'
'src/modules||%|hpp|%|%|%' 'src/modules|$(path)|$(file)|meta.$(suffix)'
